{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17508095","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17508095"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:02:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:02:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2716"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2716","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2716"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.06,0.04,0.62,0.25]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2716"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82727"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2716","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2716"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2716"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67862"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"432"},{"type":"tags","id":"2076"},{"type":"tags","id":"3504"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4963"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"8916"},{"type":"tags","id":"9022"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11636"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3425"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3426"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3487"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28288"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42553"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43988"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82727","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/82727"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a four-month history of gradually deteriorating vision in both eyes. His medical history includes hypertension and type 1 diabetes. His medications include insulin and amlodipine. On examination, his visual acuity is 6/12 in the left eye and 6/18 in the right. Fundoscopy is performed, revealing signs of diabetic retinopathy (Image). Optical coherence tomography identifies areas of retinal thickening.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Aspirin","Sitagliptin (DPP-4 inhibitor)","Intravitreal triamcinolone (corticosteroid)","Intravitreal aflibercept (anti-VEGF)","Laser photocoagulation"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThere is evidence of diabetic retinopathy from the fundus image. Dot blot haemorrhages and hard exudates near the macula are suggestive of diabetic macular edema (DME), and this is confirmed by the optical coherence tomography showing evidence of retinal swelling.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDiabetic macular edema is a complication associated with diabetic retinopathy. Diabetic retinopathy can result in the formation of new vessels which are weak and can leak plasma constituents into the retina, leading to diabetic macular edema. Vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) is upregulated in diabetic retinopathy and DME.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is no role for \u003Cstrong\u003Easpirin\u003C/strong\u003E in patients with diabetic retinopathy. \u003Cstrong\u003ESitagliptin\u003C/strong\u003E is a DPP-4 inhibitor used to treat diabetes. Before commencing on this, we would need to further assess the patient\u0027s current glycaemic control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELaser photocoagulation\u003C/strong\u003E has been traditionally used as first-line therapy for treating leaking microaneurysms that contribute to retinal oedema. However, recent evidence suggests anti-VEGF therapy with \u003Cstrong\u003Eintravitreal aflibercept\u003C/strong\u003E is superior in preventing and improving vision in patients with DME than laser photocoagulation. \u003Cstrong\u003EIntravitreal triamcinolone\u003C/strong\u003E may also be used for diabetic macular oedema, however, it is not as effective as anti-VEGF therapy and is associated with an increased risk of cataracts and higher intraocular pressure.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Intravitreal anti-VEGF therapy is the first-line therapy for diabetic macular edema.","Diabetic macular edema is a common cause of vision loss in patients with diabetic retinopathy.","Optical coherence tomography is a key diagnostic tool for identifying retinal thickening in diabetic macular edema."],"references":["Virgili G, Parravano M, Evans JR, Gordon I, Lucenteforte E. Anti-vascular endothelial growth factor for diabetic macular oedema: a network meta-analysis. Cochrane Database Syst Rev. 2017;6(6):CD007419. Available at: https://www.cochranelibrary.com/cdsr/doi/10.1002/14651858.CD007419.pub7/abstract","Kriechbaum K, Prager S, Mylonas G, et al. Intravitreal bevacizumab (Avastin) versus triamcinolone (Volon A) for treatment of diabetic macular edema: One-year results. Eye (Lond). 2014;28(1):9-16. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3890767/#:~:text=Conclusion,than%20in%20the%20triamcinolone%20sample.","Zur D, Iglicki M, Loewenstein A. The Role of Steroids in the Management of Diabetic Macular Edema. Ophthalmic Res. 2019;62(4):231-236. Available at: https://karger.com/ore/article/62/4/231/266249/The-Role-of-Steroids-in-the-Management-of-Diabetic"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67862"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2716"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"1836"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"1836","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/1836